<activity permid="yED" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="act-2-5-1">
  <statement>
    <p permid="JdI">
      For each function given below,
      identify an inner function <m>g</m> and outer function <m>f</m> to write the function in the form <m>f(g(x))</m>.
      Determine <m>f'(x)</m>, <m>g'(x)</m>, and <m>f'(g(x))</m>,
      and then apply the chain rule to determine the derivative of the given function.

      <ol permid="zac" label="a." cols="2">
        <li permid="fhl">
          <p permid="xUJ">
            <m>h(x) = \cos(x^4)</m>
          </p>
        </li>

        <li permid="Lou">
          <p permid="ebS">
            <m>p(x) = \sqrt{ \tan(x) }</m>
          </p>
        </li>

        <li permid="rvD">
          <p permid="Kjb">
            <m>s(x) = 2^{\sin(x)}</m>
          </p>
        </li>

        <li permid="XCM">
          <p permid="qqk">
            <m>z(x) = \cot^5(x)</m>
          </p>
        </li>

        <li permid="DJV">
          <p permid="Wxt">
            <m>m(x) = (\sec(x) + e^x)^9</m>
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </p>
  </statement>
  <hint permid="axs">
    <p permid="cWz">
      <ol permid="SST" label="a.">
        <li permid="jRe">
          <p permid="CEC">
            The outer function is <m>f(x) = \cos(x)</m>.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li permid="PYn">
          <p permid="iLL">
            The outer function is <m>f(x) = \sqrt{x}</m>.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li permid="wfw">
          <p permid="OSU">
            The outer function is <m>f(x) = 2^x</m>.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li permid="cmF">
          <p permid="vad">
            The outer function is <m>f(x) = x^5</m>.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li permid="ItO">
          <p permid="bhm">
            The outer function is <m>f(x) = x^9</m>.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </p>
  </hint>
  <answer permid="uqj">
    <p permid="wPq">
      <ol permid="mLK" label="a.">
        <li permid="oAX">
          <p permid="Hov">
            <m> h'(x) = -4x^3\sin(x^4)</m>.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li permid="UIg">
          <p permid="nvE">
            <m> h'(x) = \frac{\sec^2(x)}{2\sqrt{\tan(x)}}</m>.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li permid="APp">
          <p permid="TCN">
            <m> h'(x) = 2^{\sin(x)}\ln(2)\cos(x)</m>.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li permid="gWy">
          <p permid="zJW">
            <m> h'(x) = -5\cot^4(x) \csc^2(x)</m>.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li permid="NdH">
          <p permid="fRf">
            <m> h'(x) = 9(\sec(x)+e^x)^8 (\sec(x)\tan(x) + e^x)</m>.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </p>
  </answer>
  <solution permid="Oja">
    <p permid="QIh">
      <ol permid="GEB" label="a.">
        <li permid="tkQ">
          <p permid="LYo">
            The outer function is <m>f(x) = \cos(x)</m>,
            while the inner function is <m>g(x) = x^4</m>, and we know that
            <me permid="pkR">
              f'(x) = -\sin(x),
              g'(x) = 4x^3, \ \text{and}  \ f'(g(x)) = -\sin(x^4)
            </me>.
            Hence, by the chain rule,
            <me permid="Vsa">
              h'(x) = f'(g(x))g'(x) = -4x^3\sin(x^4)
            </me>.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li permid="ZrZ">
          <p permid="sfx">
            The outer function is <m>f(x) = \sqrt{x}</m>,
            while the inner function is <m>g(x) = \tan(x)</m>,
            and we know that
            <me permid="Bzj">
              f'(x) = \frac{1}{2\sqrt{x}}, g'(x) = \sec^2(x), \ \text{and}  \ f'(g(x)) = \frac{1}{2\sqrt{\tan(x)}}
            </me>.
            Hence, by the chain rule,
            <me permid="hGs">
              h'(x) = f'(g(x))g'(x) = \frac{\sec^2(x)}{2\sqrt{\tan(x)}}
            </me>.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li permid="Fzi">
          <p permid="YmG">
            The outer function is <m>f(x) = 2^x</m>,
            while the inner function is <m>g(x) = \sin(x)</m>,
            and we know that
            <me permid="NNB">
              f'(x) = 2^x \ln(2),
              g'(x) = \cos(x), \ \text{and}  \ f'(g(x)) = 2^{\sin(x)}\ln(2)
            </me>.
            Hence, by the chain rule,
            <me permid="tUK">
              h'(x) = f'(g(x))g'(x) = 2^{\sin(x)}\ln(2)\cos(x)
            </me>.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li permid="lGr">
          <p permid="EtP">
            The outer function is <m>f(x) = x^5</m>,
            while the inner function is <m>g(x) = \cot(x)</m>,
            and we know that
            <me permid="abT">
              f'(x) = 5x^4, g'(x) = -\csc^2(x), \ \text{and}  \ f'(g(x)) = 5\cot^4(x)
            </me>.
            Hence, by the chain rule,
            <me permid="Gjc">
              h'(x) = f'(g(x))g'(x) = -5\cot^4(x) \csc^2(x)
            </me>.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li permid="RNA">
          <p permid="kAY">
            The outer function is <m>f(x) = x^9</m>,
            while the inner function is <m>g(x) = \sec(x) + e^x</m>,
            and we know that
            <me permid="mql">
              f'(x) = 9x^8, g'(x) = \sec(x)\tan(x) + e^x, \ \text{and}  \ f'(g(x)) = 9(\sec(x)+e^x)^8
            </me>.
            Hence, by the chain rule,
            <me permid="Sxu">
              h'(x) = f'(g(x))g'(x) = 9(\sec(x)+e^x)^8 (\sec(x)\tan(x) + e^x)
            </me>.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </p>
  </solution>
</activity>

